WEBVTT

00:05.650 --> 00:09.160
Is an athlete an athlete 
from the day they are born?

00:09.950 --> 00:12.690
What about an astronaut or an idol?

00:14.140 --> 00:16.250
You can't know what you'll be at birth.

00:17.380 --> 00:20.380
Then... what about witches?

01:20.870 --> 01:23.850
Oh. Sorry for the mess.

01:23.850 --> 01:25.680
I'm just about finished with my laundry.

01:29.170 --> 01:30.880
It'll go back to normal soon.

01:31.330 --> 01:34.310
This spring is touched by magic!

01:58.490 --> 02:00.870
It's beautiful every time I see it.

02:00.870 --> 02:03.630
Magic is so amazing!

02:07.000 --> 02:12.930
<i>The world brims with magic, 
an essential and handy miracle.</i>

02:14.910 --> 02:19.580
<b>The Magic that Started Everything</b>

02:14.970 --> 02:17.540
<i>But how it works is unknown.</i>

02:18.780 --> 02:22.410
<i>Witches are the only ones
who can cast spells,</i>

02:23.980 --> 02:28.140
<i>and ordinary people can 
only be blessed with it.</i>

02:29.250 --> 02:31.510
<i>Not everyone can become a witch.</i>

02:34.510 --> 02:38.230
Must be nice being born a witch.

02:45.530 --> 02:47.420
O sheets, O sheets...

02:47.420 --> 02:50.750
I command you to turn 
into a flying cloak!

02:55.650 --> 02:56.730
Oh! Wait!

02:56.730 --> 02:59.160
That's not what I meant by "flying"!

03:15.900 --> 03:17.260
It's a Pegasus Carriage!

03:31.060 --> 03:33.570
I've never seen one land before!

03:35.910 --> 03:39.350
Mom! There's a Pegasus Carriage outside!

03:40.320 --> 03:41.830
Mom!

03:43.170 --> 03:45.300
Mom!

03:52.590 --> 03:54.840
I'm sorry! I didn't know you were there.

03:55.170 --> 03:58.680
It's okay. It's on me 
for standing by the door.

03:58.680 --> 04:00.650
Oh, my. I can't believe it!

04:00.650 --> 04:03.590
Look! Who'd have thought this place 
would have something like this?

04:03.590 --> 04:07.160
Oh, but isn't wood-sorrel 
embroidery a bit dated?

04:07.160 --> 04:10.450
You won't believe what I found! 
This is Harrian lace.

04:10.450 --> 04:14.370
Oh, amazing! It sold out 
in no time in the castle town.

04:14.370 --> 04:17.940
We were right to travel 
all this way by Pegasus Carriage.

04:15.350 --> 04:18.750
They're the people who came 
in the Pegasus Carriage!

04:20.310 --> 04:22.120
Oh, no. I'm not with them.

04:22.430 --> 04:25.720
Excuse me. Do you have 
any more lace like this?

04:25.720 --> 04:27.460
Yes, certainly!

04:27.460 --> 04:29.450
Look, this one's so cute, too!

04:28.440 --> 04:30.540
Coco, don't just stand there. 
Help out!

04:30.540 --> 04:31.690
How about this one?

04:32.250 --> 04:34.000
Sir, what can we help you with?

04:34.000 --> 04:36.150
I'm looking for some smoke-colored fabric.

04:36.150 --> 04:37.800
But I can come back later if you're busy.

04:37.800 --> 04:39.720
I can take care of the cutting for you.

04:39.720 --> 04:40.720
You can?

04:40.720 --> 04:42.650
She's got a good handle on it.

04:42.010 --> 04:43.550
It's lovely!

04:42.650 --> 04:44.140
Wow.

04:47.250 --> 04:49.850
Can I go see the Pegasus 
Carriage after I'm done?

04:49.850 --> 04:51.170
Say what?

04:51.170 --> 04:52.690
There's a Pegasus Carriage outside!

04:53.190 --> 04:54.520
A Pegasus Carriage?

04:54.520 --> 04:57.550
You'd better not be thinking of 
messing with the customers' things.

04:57.550 --> 04:59.400
Don't worry. I'm just gonna look!

05:01.650 --> 05:05.330
I won't say I want to be a witch anymore.

05:09.530 --> 05:11.870
If you finish up early, sure.

05:11.870 --> 05:13.540
Yes!

05:14.460 --> 05:17.080
Thank you for waiting. 
What are the measurements?

05:17.080 --> 05:18.400
Oh, I wrote it down.

05:18.400 --> 05:20.050
Thank you.

05:59.820 --> 06:00.920
Wow.

06:02.330 --> 06:05.800
You've got great concentration. 
And you've got steady hands.

06:05.800 --> 06:08.930
No hesitation in the line, clean cut...

06:08.930 --> 06:11.690
and such a careful, precise finish.

06:12.350 --> 06:15.490
I had no idea this village had 
such a skilled craftsman.

06:17.090 --> 06:18.570
This is real magic.

06:19.940 --> 06:24.450
N-N-N-N-N-N-N-No! 
It's nothing like that at all!

06:24.450 --> 06:27.280
Magic is way more mysterious and sparkly!

06:27.280 --> 06:29.450
It's valuable and really pretty.

06:29.450 --> 06:32.600
And it's something that's more... more...

06:33.020 --> 06:36.580
Something truly p-precious.

06:37.050 --> 06:39.310
What am I saying?

06:39.810 --> 06:42.130
You really like magic, don't you?

06:44.520 --> 06:46.640
Mind if I ask why you like it so much?

06:52.260 --> 06:56.410
When I was little, 
I went to a festival at the castle,

06:56.920 --> 07:00.150
and I met a witch wearing a mask.

07:17.900 --> 07:19.500
You there.

07:21.050 --> 07:23.720
Would you like to buy 
a magic picture book?

07:26.320 --> 07:27.760
Magic?

07:27.760 --> 07:31.560
I love picture books, but what's magic?

07:31.910 --> 07:36.070
Magic is a miracle 
that makes this world vibrant.

07:37.620 --> 07:40.110
A Pegasus Carriage 
that soars through the vast sky,

07:40.110 --> 07:43.150
an everlasting spring 
that preserves crystal-clear waters...

07:43.150 --> 07:46.850
Even the cobblestones beneath your feet

07:46.850 --> 07:50.820
lighting up as you walk—it's all magic.

07:52.980 --> 07:54.700
So pwetty!

07:54.700 --> 07:58.820
I like magic!

07:58.820 --> 08:01.460
It comes with a free wand, too.

08:04.810 --> 08:07.720
And you ended up buying that?

08:08.050 --> 08:10.670
But you said you wanted 
the roasted strawberries.

08:10.670 --> 08:15.210
When I followed a butterfly, 
there was a person with a pointed hat.

08:15.210 --> 08:17.300
You already told me that.

08:17.300 --> 08:21.730
So it's a magical picture book! 
With a wand!

08:24.020 --> 08:26.390
Okay, then. Let's head home, Coco.

08:26.390 --> 08:27.520
It's getting late.

08:27.520 --> 08:28.730
Mommy!

08:29.240 --> 08:34.990
When I grow up, I'm gonna be a witch 
that makes our world vibrant!

08:34.990 --> 08:36.200
You can't.

08:36.200 --> 08:37.550
Why not?

08:38.540 --> 08:39.370
Listen, Coco.

08:39.880 --> 08:45.230
You can't become a witch unless 
you're born with magical powers.

08:45.880 --> 08:49.770
Ordinary people don't have 
what it takes to be a witch.

08:51.540 --> 08:53.450
Now, let's go home.

08:53.450 --> 08:54.470
But look!

08:55.120 --> 08:57.720
The ground shines 
every time I take a step!

09:00.640 --> 09:05.070
If the ground shines all the way home,

09:05.460 --> 09:08.090
then maybe you'll be 
able to use magic, too.

09:17.660 --> 09:20.820
Since then, I've sort of 
grown fond of watching magic.

09:20.820 --> 09:22.920
I can't let go of my dream 
of becoming a witch.

09:22.920 --> 09:25.420
Could you tell me a little more about—

09:26.960 --> 09:28.350
What was that?

09:29.090 --> 09:29.970
Coco?

09:29.970 --> 09:32.490
Hey, now, settle down.

09:33.230 --> 09:34.900
There, there.

09:44.350 --> 09:46.470
Look what you've done. Sheesh.

09:46.470 --> 09:48.430
Shut up... Ow.

09:48.430 --> 09:49.590
Are you guys all right?

09:49.590 --> 09:50.590
Coco.

09:50.590 --> 09:52.050
What happened?

09:52.050 --> 09:54.240
We didn't do anything. 
It fell apart on its own.

09:54.240 --> 09:57.380
Liar! You crawled underneath it!

09:57.380 --> 09:58.790
You snitch!

09:58.790 --> 10:01.370
He hit his head, and it fell over.

10:01.370 --> 10:03.500
Oh, my! How awful!

10:04.060 --> 10:06.040
Look what you've done 
to our Pegasus Carriage!

10:06.040 --> 10:08.300
It was our father's.

10:08.300 --> 10:12.050
I'm terribly sorry for the awful 
trouble they've caused you!

10:12.320 --> 10:14.270
A-Apologizing won't change anything.

10:14.270 --> 10:16.410
We can't go back home without a carriage!

10:16.410 --> 10:18.310
Oh, my... What should we do?

10:19.370 --> 10:20.460
Pardon me.

10:22.730 --> 10:24.230
Would you like me to fix it?

10:25.910 --> 10:28.980
From what I can see, 
the damage isn't too bad.

10:28.980 --> 10:31.230
And who are you supposed to be?

10:31.500 --> 10:34.800
My apologies. It would help 
if I had my signature hat on.

10:40.990 --> 10:44.430
My name is Qifrey. I am a witch.

10:47.380 --> 10:49.230
The pointed hat.

10:49.750 --> 10:51.000
So you can fix our carriage?

10:51.000 --> 10:52.280
Absolutely.

10:52.280 --> 10:54.780
You're a lifesaver, Mr. Witch.

10:54.780 --> 10:55.970
It's not a big deal.

10:56.490 --> 10:59.420
I'll just reapply the spell 
to the carriage's floorboard.

10:59.420 --> 11:01.590
We'd love to ask for your help!

11:01.590 --> 11:03.190
At your service.

11:03.190 --> 11:05.260
However, doing it outdoors 
might be a bit—

11:05.260 --> 11:07.690
Y-Y-You can use our workshop!

11:07.690 --> 11:08.710
Hey, Coco!

11:09.040 --> 11:10.610
Come on, Mom!

11:12.080 --> 11:13.110
<i>I mean...</i>

11:13.680 --> 11:16.110
<i>He's a real witch.</i>

11:17.190 --> 11:19.810
<i>This might be my chance</i>

11:20.790 --> 11:23.630
<i>to see the exact moment 
of a spell being cast.</i>

11:32.490 --> 11:34.320
Will you keep watch outside

11:34.320 --> 11:38.120
and make sure no one looks 
in while I'm casting the spell?

11:38.540 --> 11:41.140
No matter what happens, 
don't let anyone come inside.

11:41.140 --> 11:42.180
Understood?

11:45.150 --> 11:47.770
Life isn't that easy, huh?

11:48.770 --> 11:51.770
<i>But why can't we watch how it's done?</i>

11:52.730 --> 11:55.970
<i>Magic is all over the world,</i>

11:55.970 --> 11:58.850
<i>yet we don't know how it's cast.</i>

11:59.360 --> 12:01.660
<i>Witches are the only ones 
who know the secret.</i>

12:02.410 --> 12:03.820
The secret...

12:10.410 --> 12:11.500
Huh?

12:11.500 --> 12:12.740
Whoa, it's slippery!

12:14.800 --> 12:16.660
Hey! What do you think you're doing?

12:16.660 --> 12:17.550
She found us!

12:17.550 --> 12:19.300
She's nothing. We're fine.

12:19.300 --> 12:21.270
Can we see the room from here?

12:22.300 --> 12:23.210
Wait for me!

12:23.210 --> 12:24.830
Lower your voice!

12:24.830 --> 12:26.560
Move over!

12:38.940 --> 12:40.920
Bleh, no fun.

12:40.920 --> 12:42.490
Seriously, man.

12:50.450 --> 12:51.460
What's going on?!

13:22.870 --> 13:24.300
<i>I really shouldn't!</i>

13:24.300 --> 13:26.240
<i>But I really wanna see it!</i>

13:26.240 --> 13:27.120
<i>But I shouldn't!</i>

13:54.700 --> 13:56.300
He's drawing...

14:00.310 --> 14:03.170
He's drawing magic with a pen?

14:05.170 --> 14:09.250
Then... that wasn't a wand...

14:11.010 --> 14:15.140
Spells aren't something you cast...

14:16.870 --> 14:18.060
but something you draw!

14:19.750 --> 14:20.920
That should do.

14:20.920 --> 14:22.970
Coco, I'm done.

14:31.360 --> 14:32.350
Coco?

14:32.350 --> 14:33.610
Thank you for your hard work.

14:33.610 --> 14:34.620
Uh-huh...

14:52.110 --> 14:54.780
I'm a bit relieved, you know.

14:55.540 --> 14:57.950
You love magic so much,

14:58.470 --> 15:04.730
so I thought you'd say you 
wanted to go with that witch.

15:06.160 --> 15:08.550
I lost your father to illness.

15:08.870 --> 15:13.060
So if you left me too, I'd...

15:13.060 --> 15:16.940
I won't! I won't leave you 
by yourself, Mom!

15:20.150 --> 15:24.040
Thanks. You're such a sweet girl, Coco.

15:42.310 --> 15:43.590
Goodnight.

15:43.870 --> 15:45.360
Goodnight.

15:45.360 --> 15:46.710
Oh, Coco.

15:49.680 --> 15:52.220
Never mind. Sweet dreams.

15:52.910 --> 15:54.220
You, too.

16:02.730 --> 16:05.990
I thought you'd say you 
wanted to go with that witch.

16:23.550 --> 16:26.460
<i>The patterns drawn all over 
the magic picture book.</i>

16:27.000 --> 16:30.290
<i>The wand wasn't just a bonus 
that came with the book.</i>

16:31.180 --> 16:34.150
<i>The pen itself was the magic wand!</i>

16:47.850 --> 16:51.600
<i>Sorry, Mom... I won't go anywhere.</i>

16:52.160 --> 16:53.220
<i>Just let me try it out.</i>

17:43.000 --> 17:43.980
Huh?

17:46.580 --> 17:49.210
Bummer, nothing's happening.

17:49.210 --> 17:52.470
Yeah, it couldn't be that easy.

18:18.860 --> 18:21.540
It sparkled! I actually used magic!

18:21.540 --> 18:24.220
Wow, magic! I used magic! Real magic!

18:24.220 --> 18:26.010
It worked! Oh my gosh!

18:26.870 --> 18:28.700
So magic <i>is</i> something you draw.

18:28.700 --> 18:31.590
But I wasn't supposed to see it. 
Will he get mad if he finds out?

18:31.590 --> 18:32.750
Ugh...

18:36.600 --> 18:39.710
But let's draw one more. Just one more...

18:53.410 --> 18:56.280
<i>A picture book... A picture book, huh?</i>

18:57.870 --> 19:00.150
<i>It bugs me.</i>

19:02.990 --> 19:04.110
Could it be?!

19:06.190 --> 19:08.140
Wow! That one was a fire spell!

19:08.140 --> 19:10.020
No, stop burning!

19:11.580 --> 19:13.550
Phew, that was close.

19:14.800 --> 19:15.800
But...

19:17.550 --> 19:19.820
I think I'm starting 
to get the hang of it.

19:20.310 --> 19:23.560
Bigger ones are stronger 
than smaller ones.

19:23.560 --> 19:26.890
And neatly drawn ones 
last longer than sloppy ones.

19:27.620 --> 19:30.720
But drawing it big and neat is so hard.

19:31.020 --> 19:33.400
That man made it look so easy.

19:34.110 --> 19:35.070
I know!

19:40.120 --> 19:41.750
<i>Just as I thought.</i>

19:41.750 --> 19:45.580
<i>I can draw it neatly 
by tracing over the example.</i>

19:54.940 --> 19:56.180
There!

20:16.910 --> 20:18.110
You drew magic, didn't you?!

20:18.110 --> 20:21.240
What did you draw?! 
What kind of spell did you draw?!

20:21.240 --> 20:24.740
I don't know. I just traced the pattern 
that was in the picture book.

20:24.740 --> 20:25.800
Coco?

20:28.610 --> 20:29.670
Mom!

20:33.970 --> 20:35.110
Coco?!

20:35.670 --> 20:36.590
Run!

20:42.800 --> 20:44.850
Mom... No...

20:45.470 --> 20:49.140
Mom! Mom! Mom!

20:49.140 --> 20:50.530
Mom!

20:49.140 --> 20:50.900
<i>This is... forbidden magic!</i>

20:50.900 --> 20:52.230
No! Let go of me!

20:52.230 --> 20:54.510
Let go! Let go!

20:52.230 --> 20:54.510
No! You'll get caught up in it, too!

20:54.510 --> 20:56.080
I have to save my mom!

20:56.080 --> 20:57.650
It's no use! It's a spell!

20:57.650 --> 20:58.980
And an evil one—

20:58.980 --> 21:00.120
Shoot!

21:05.350 --> 21:06.080
Coco!

21:06.080 --> 21:07.560
Mom!

21:09.210 --> 21:10.940
No!

21:15.680 --> 21:19.220
I'm sorry... I didn't know...

21:19.670 --> 21:21.670
Of course you didn't.

21:22.160 --> 21:24.720
It was kept a secret so 
nothing like this would happen.

21:25.540 --> 21:29.130
A special ink and a set of Casting Seals.

21:29.130 --> 21:31.970
That's all anyone needs to use magic.

21:31.970 --> 21:34.730
It's the One Great Rule of witches.

21:35.520 --> 21:39.240
And now that you've found out, 
I must erase your memories.

21:43.040 --> 21:44.450
Please don't!

21:44.450 --> 21:48.120
If I forget everything, 
who will save my mom?!

21:48.760 --> 21:50.620
It's very unfortunate.

21:51.260 --> 21:53.250
I don't remember what 
kind of magic I drew,

21:53.250 --> 21:56.160
but I know what was written 
in the picture book by heart!

21:56.160 --> 21:58.680
And if I forget that, my mom is...

21:59.940 --> 22:01.130
The picture book?

22:01.670 --> 22:03.030
<i>That's right.</i>

22:03.030 --> 22:06.930
<i>If that picture book belonged to </i>them<i>, 
I'll be losing track of their whereabouts!</i>

22:07.650 --> 22:11.090
<i>I'll have no way to trace them 
if I erase her memory!</i>

22:11.980 --> 22:14.380
You remember the book by heart, correct?

22:15.550 --> 22:17.590
And which page you copied?

22:19.880 --> 22:24.220
Oh! If we can find the same book, 
we can find the Casting Seal I drew.

22:26.950 --> 22:31.370
Can we save my mom if we find 
which Casting Seal it was?

22:33.960 --> 22:35.260
There's still...

22:35.760 --> 22:37.060
a chance.

22:37.570 --> 22:38.800
Mr. Qifrey!

22:39.740 --> 22:45.360
Please don't erase my memories! 
I'll do anything to save my mom!

22:47.300 --> 22:49.180
Can you keep the secret?

22:49.180 --> 22:50.460
I can!

22:52.040 --> 22:53.850
Are you willing to learn?

22:53.850 --> 22:55.870
Learn... What?

22:56.330 --> 22:59.100
Once you know the truth, 
it can't be undone.

22:59.100 --> 23:02.860
In that case, you must become 
one of those who know the secret.

23:03.440 --> 23:06.750
That is the only way for you 
to keep your memories.

23:08.160 --> 23:09.350
Coco.

23:09.350 --> 23:10.880
From now on,

23:12.500 --> 23:14.510
you are going to become a witch.

23:35.390 --> 23:39.980
Episode 2:

23:35.390 --> 23:39.980
The School of the Grassland
